-- House expects to reconvene at noon Tuesday - Representative LaTourette
-- 
-- Mon Dec 31, 2012 5:58pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/31/us-usa-fiscal-house-latourette-idUSBRE8BU0H120121231

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The U.S. House of Representatives expects to reconvene on Tuesday at noon, Representative Steven LaTourette said, after negotiations to avert the "fiscal cliff" developed slowly on Monday. 
 LaTourette, a Republican, also said that House members have been told to stay close on Monday evening and that they may be called back to continue negotiations. (Reporting by  Rachelle Younglai ; Editing by  Will Dunham )